-- note: soft cell evaluated via ∴ (LLM). oracles checked inline.

⊢ topic
  yield subject ≡ "the moon"

⊢ compose
  given topic→subject ≡ "the moon"
  yield poem ≡ "Silver light descends\nIlluminating the lake\nSilence answers back"

  ∴ Write a haiku about «subject».
    A haiku has exactly 3 lines: 5 syllables, 7 syllables, 5 syllables.

  ⊨ poem has exactly 3 lines ✓
  ⊨ poem line 1 has 5 syllables ✓
  ⊨ poem line 2 has 7 syllables ✓
  ⊨ poem line 3 has 5 syllables ✓

⊢ count-lines
  given compose→poem ≡ "Silver light descends\nIlluminating the lake\nSilence answers back"
  yield n-lines
  ⊢= n-lines ← len(split(poem, "\n"))

  ⊨ n-lines = 3

⊢ reflect
  given compose→poem ≡ "Silver light descends\nIlluminating the lake\nSilence answers back"
  given count-lines→n-lines
  given topic→subject ≡ "the moon"
  yield reflection

  ∴ Does this haiku about «subject» evoke an image or feeling?
    Poem: «poem»
    Give a one-sentence assessment.

  ⊨ reflection is non-empty
